# Record architecture decisions

Date: 2021-04-28

## Status

Proposed

## Context

1. We need to accept tickets and response back success to customer. L
2.  lost tickets


## Decision

1. We will write to No SQL DB, so that we can handle the large number of request. 
2. Add Queue. Push the ticket to queue 
3. Load balancing
## Consequences

See Michael Nygard's article, linked above. For a lightweight ADR toolset, see Nat Pryce's [adr-tools](https://github.com/npryce/adr-tools).

**Positive:**  Solves the problem related to spike in request.
All tickets are captured in queue

**Negative:** If any

